ANTHRAX, BOVINE - SLOVAKIA: (PRESOV) 2010, OIE
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 14 Mar 2011
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2011; 24(11) [edited]
<http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=10361>


Anthrax, Slovakia
-----------------
Information received on (and dated) 14 Mar 2011 from Dr Jozef Bires,
director & chief veterinary officer, State Veterinary and Food
Administration, Ministry of Agriculture, Bratislava, Slovakia

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no. 2 (final report)
Start date: 9 Jul 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 9 Jul 2010
Report date: 14 Mar 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 14 Mar 2011
Date event resolved: 10 Aug 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1995
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to: the whole country
Related reports
- Immediate notification (13 Jul 2010)
- Follow-up report no. 1 (21 Jul 2010)
- Follow-up report no. 2 (14 Mar 2011)

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (2010/3): Okruhle, Svidnik, Svidnik, Presov
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Jul 2010
Outbreak status: resolved (10 Aug 2010)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species: Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle: 134 / 1 /1 / 1 / 0
Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case
fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.75 percent / 0.75 percent / 100 percent / 1.49 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: control of wildlife reservoirs; quarantine;
disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no vaccination; no
treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: State Veterinary and Food Institute (SVFI),
Dolny Kubin (national laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 28 Jul 2010 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
Castleview Pedigree English Longhorns
Gut Laach
52385 Nideggen
